How do Build Forge Eclipse IDE plug-ins enable Pre-Flight builds?
A. through configuration of the Eclipse Build Forge Perspective
B. through configuration of the Eclipse Build Forge Project Artifacts properties
C. by configuring Eclipse to use Dynamic Views for integration builds
D. through build status reporting via the Eclipse Build Forge Frequency Plug-In
Answer: B
What should you do to allocate more console resources for running jobs?
A. adjust the Active Server Refresh Interval to a higher time value than the default
B. adjust the Database Size Threshold to a value smaller than the default
C. set the Hard Run Limit
D. increase the value for Server Retries
Answer: A
